Reasoning: The paper deals with mobile robots and their ability to navigate and avoid obstacles, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The method proposed involves using neural networks to learn a mapping from raw 2D laser data to obstacle distances, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of neural networks also falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper demonstrates the method on a Care-O-bot 4, which is a robotic system, and therefore falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
